# USER — Preferences and Profile

Durable facts about *the person talking to the agent*: name, role, tone
preferences, recurring contexts. Loaded once per session and wrapped in
`<user_profile>` tags in the system prompt. Soft cap ~1,375 chars to keep
the prompt cache warm.

The agent maintains this file via the `memory` tool
(`action="add" | "replace" | "list"`). You can also edit it by hand.

Format: one fact per `§`-delimited block. Keep entries dense — no
narrative prose.

---

§ Name: <your name>
§ Pronouns: <they/she/he>
§ Time zone: <e.g. America/Los_Angeles>
§ Tone preference: terse, no filler, no "great question!"
§ Don't repeat the user's question back before answering.
